{"type":"message","id":"c99d0fcf","parentId":"83ef0506","timestamp":"2026-04-05T15:24:25.773Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user sent \"ddd\" which is a Chinese message that could mean:\n1. \"弟弟\" (dìdi) - younger brother\n2. \"等等\" (děngděng) - wait a moment\n3. \"滴滴\" (dīdī) - beep beep (sound)\n4. Could be a typo or informal greeting\n\nGiven the context of a direct message on Feishu, it's most likely \"等等\" (wait) or just a casual acknowledgment. However, it could also be someone testing or just saying \"hi\" in an informal way.\n\nI should respond naturally and ask what they need help with.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n收到！有什么需要帮忙的吗？🦐"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":10858,"output":144,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":11002,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775402663299,"responseId":"chatcmpl-0f63110d-5dd4-4d0e-a6d5-60ee51885d07"}}
